Abdomen
. Abdomen slightly petiolate, narrow and elongated, sometimes petiolate; terga 3 and 4 with medial, pale, triangular maculae that might be incised posteriorly or fully divided medially into two short stripes (
Fig. 50
). 
Terminalia
. Male postgonite apical margin straight and with dorsal and ventral apical acute extremities (
Fig. 56
); surstylus with homogenously distributed setulae ventrally; hypandrium with pile sub-apically on ventro-lateral surface; basiphallus teardrop-shaped, distiphallus membranous with dorsal sclerotized triangular region (similar to 
Fig. 97
).
